  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>pork steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature, then boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped sweet potato</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> over a high heat and bring to the boil</p><p>Cook for 10-12 min or until fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1719319944072-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1719319944072-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1719319944072-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1719319944072-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1719319944072-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>pork loin steak[s]</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half </strong>your <strong>jerk paste</strong>,<strong> half </strong>your<strong> white wine vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>flour</strong></p><p>Add a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>jerk-spiced pork</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1719319950753-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1719319950753-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1719319950753-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1719319950753-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1719319950753-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>jerk-spiced pork</strong> and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until slightly charred and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1719319958272-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1719319958272-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1719319958272-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
