            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1719319982458-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pork is done, transfer the <strong>cooked steak</strong> to a clean chopping board (reserve the pan!) and leave to rest for 2 min</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-heat with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>and stir for 30 secs</p><p>Gradually stir in the <strong>jerk-spiced stock </strong>and cook for 2 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains – this is your <strong>jerk-spiced sauce</strong></p><p>Tip: Scrape any bits from the bottom of the pan as this will add extra flavour to the sauce!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1723624486768-x200.jpg",
